Four people were trapped in the wreckage of a car which collided with an electricity pole on Sunday - with three of them taken to hospital.Firefighters from Buckley and Deeside were called to the incident on Kinnerton Road, Higher Kinnerton in Flintshire at 21:12 BST.Hydraulic cutting gear was used to free the people in the vehicle.Police and the Welsh Ambulance Service also attended.
